l. 30. Henrico quondam . . . episcopo. Henry of Blois (c. noo—1 171), brother of King Stephen and bishop of Winchester (1129-1171). It seems possible that Richard the treasurer cites him as the source of his information by way of implying that it was not derived from Roget of Salisbury. Henry’s age and his residence at Winchester would give a special value to his statement.
